Exercise catalog data
======================

The exercise data embedded in catalog.json (names, muscle groups, equipment,
Italian instructions) and the animation GIFs referenced by it are derived from:

    hasaneyldrm/exercises-dataset
    https://github.com/hasaneyldrm/exercises-dataset
    pinned commit: f987a7b858d7987c3677e1073ee18b623895f615

The upstream repository states its content is for "educational and non-commercial
research purposes only" and that the exercise media belong to their respective
copyright holders.

Honest posture: Cadenza is a single-athlete, personal, non-commercial project, and
this integration relies on personal-use tolerance, not a clean license chain. The
upstream "non-commercial" label is the repo author's assertion; the underlying media
were most likely sourced from a commercial fitness library, and a redistributor
cannot grant rights it never held. We therefore:

  - embed only the textual catalog (no media in this repository);
  - fetch GIFs at send time from the upstream's own public raw URL (we do not
    re-host them ourselves);
  - note that delivering a GIF through Telegram does cache it on Telegram's CDN.

If Cadenza is ever used commercially, this data and the media references must be
removed or replaced with properly licensed content.
